                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Do cab radio and speakers function properly?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Refer to Radio and Cab Speaker Troubleshooting in CAB ACCESSORIES section.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Do bunk speakers function properly?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to Step 10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect volume control connectors (122) and (123), rear bunk speaker (9), and radio
                                connector (21). At connector (9) measure resistance of speaker.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Across speaker (9).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>3.5 to 8 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective rear bunk speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Reconnect rear bunk speaker (9). At connector (123) install a jumper wire from circuit
                                86S to 86CC, and at connector (21), measure resistance from circuit 86CC to 86CD.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(21), 86CC to 86CD.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>3.5 to 8 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection if resistance is too high, or short to ground if
                                resistance is too low in circuit 86CC, 86S, or 86CD, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect front bunk speaker (10) and measure resistance of speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Across speaker (10).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>3.5 to 8 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective front bunk speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect front bunk speaker (10). At connector (122) install a jumper wire from
                                circuit 86R to 86CA, and at connector (21), measure resistance from circuit 86CA to
                                86CB.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(21) 86CA to 86CB.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>3.5 to 8 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection if resistance is too high, or short to ground if
                                resistance is too low in circuit 86CA, 86R, or 86CB, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At connector (122), move jumper wire to between circuits 86F and 86CA, and at
                                connector (21), measure resistance from circuit 86CA to 86CB.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(21), 86CA to 86CB.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 86F, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>At conn. (123), move jumper wire to between circuits 86H and 86CC, and at connector
                                (21), measure resistance from circuit 86CC to 86CD.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(21), 86CC to 86CD.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 86H, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>Remove jumpers and reconnect all connectors. Do bunk speakers function properly?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Repair or replace defective volume control panel assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
